  <section xml:id="cockpit-creating-virtual-machines-pools">
    <title>Creating storage pools</title>
    <para>
      A storage pool is designated storage devices which a virtual machine can utilize.</para>
      <para> To create a
      pool, click <guimenu>Create storage pool</guimenu>. A new popup windows opens. There you can configure
      the following items:      
      </para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guilabel>Connection</guilabel></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Specify if the pool is accessible for a regular user by selecting <guilabel>User
            session</guilabel>, or for a user with <command>sudo</command> privileges by
            selecting <guilabel>System</guilabel>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guilabel>Name</guilabel></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              Enter the pool name.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guilabel>Type</guilabel></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>The
              following storage pools are available:
            </para>
            <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guilabel>Filesystem directory</guilabel> - the pool is created in a local directory.            
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>Network file system</guilabel> - the pool is created on a NFS server.
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>iSCSI target</guilabel> -the pool is created on an iSCSI target.
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>Physical disk device</guilabel> - the pool uses a mounted physical disk.
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>LVM volume group</guilabel> - the pool is located on an LVM file system.
                </para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  <guilabel>iSCSI direct target</guilabel> - the pool is located on an iSCSI initiator.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
      
